</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/udandaeluswyldheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dandaelus Wyldheart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/19/01 7:50:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/finfinitusvindicatfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Ranger and his Bow</span><hr size=1> its all random when you will do a crit and for how much that crit will be.<br>
I have fired TS and gotten a crit of 43, then when TS wore off, gotten a crit for 282. I have also , on a regular basis, landed regular shots for more damage than my crits. I have also gone through a whole quiver of arrows with no crit whatsoever, even with a 255dex/str.<br>
<br>
I think they have a mystical x factor added into bow damage.<br>
But I do think that the higher damage the arrow you use, the higher the high crit you will get will be, plus more damage on a regular basis with normal shots. plus you will always do more damage on an opponent who snared and/or aggroed and in melle with a tank.<br>
